To analyze the sentence "Att vi lever i ett demokratiskt land är viktigt därför att alla har rätt att ha en egen åsikt, religion, etnisk bakgrund." and produce a dependency tree, we can break down the sentence as follows:

1. Att (that) - infinitive marker
2. vi (we) - subject of 'lever'
3. lever (live) - main verb of the clause (head of the clause)
4. i (in) - preposition introducing the prepositional phrase
5. ett (a) - determiner for 'land'
6. demokratiskt (democratic) - adjective describing 'land'
7. land (land) - the head noun of the prepositional phrase
8. är (is) - linking verb connecting subject to complement
9. viktigt (important) - subject complement
10. därför (therefore) - adverbial
11. att (that) - infinitive marker introducing a subordinate clause
12. alla (everyone) - subject of 'har'
13. har (has) - main verb of the subordinate clause
14. rätt (right) - direct object of 'har'
15. att (to) - infinitive marker introducing another infinitive clause
16. ha (have) - main verb 
17. en (a) - determiner for 'åsikt'
18. egen (own) - adjective describing 'åsikt'
19. åsikt (opinion) - noun
20. , (comma) - punctuation
21. religion (religion) - noun, series continuation
22. , (comma) - punctuation
23. etnisk (ethnic) - adjective describing 'bakgrund'
24. bakgrund (background) - noun

Following this structure, the dependency tree can be represented as:

```
[
  (1, Att, 2),
  (2, vi, 3),
  (3, lever, 0),
  (4, i, 5),
  (5, ett, 7),
  (6, demokratiskt, 7),
  (7, land, 3),
  (8, är, 3),
  (9, viktigt, 8),
  (10, därför, 3),
  (11, att, 12),
  (12, alla, 13),
  (13, har, 0),
  (14, rätt, 13),
  (15, att, 16),
  (16, ha, 14),
  (17, en, 19),
  (18, egen, 19),
  (19, åsikt, 16),
  (20, ,, 3),
  (21, religion, 16),
  (22, ,, 3),
  (23, etnisk, 24),
  (24, bakgrund, 16)
]
``` 

Each tuple represents a token index, the token itself, and the index of its head token.